      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Ingratiator</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael Taglieri letter on James Traub's July 30 article holds Gov George Pataki wants Rick Lazio to win US Senate race because he could be easily controlled</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>It's obvious why Gov. George Pataki wants Lazio to be the next senator from New York. With no strongly held beliefs, few opinions on any subject and no apparent intellectual gifts, Lazio would be easy for the governor to control. Why we, the voters, would want such a nonentity to represent us is a more difficult question, and I hope people will give it some thought before the election rather than afterward.</p>
        <p>Michael Taglieri  New York</p>
      </block>
